WEBVTT

00:01.484 --> 00:04.113
Who knows better
about Mr. Tree...

00:04.196 --> 00:09.952
than our bestest buddy,
Ruff the Bear?

00:11.203 --> 00:13.038
I ain't taking no orders
from no chipmunk.

00:13.163 --> 00:16.667
Let's do it. I want to waste
that chipmunk once and for all.

00:17.459 --> 00:20.337
I send you out
to whack a chipmunk...

00:20.420 --> 00:22.381
and you come back
with a mouthful of excuses.

00:22.464 --> 00:24.967
You can't hurt me.
You can't hurt my people.

00:26.760 --> 00:28.387
They're snatching
Uncle Buckle-Up!

00:28.428 --> 00:31.807
Why would somebody resort to
kidnapping over a few stuffed animals?

00:31.932 --> 00:35.018
Their heads are not supposed to come
off until we want them to come off.

00:35.144 --> 00:37.062
Then we'll take care
of all of them.

00:37.312 --> 00:38.814
All of them, including...

00:38.897 --> 00:40.357
Chipmunks are a dime a dozen.

00:40.440 --> 00:43.527
An actor can tell when his
career's coming to an end.

00:46.989 --> 00:49.491
<i>In 1972,
a crack commando unit...</i>

00:49.616 --> 00:51.160
<i>was sent to prison
by a military court...</i>

00:51.285 --> 00:52.661
<i>for a crime they didn't commit.</i>

00:52.786 --> 00:53.912
<i>These men promptly escaped...</i>

00:54.037 --> 00:55.622
<i>from a maximum-security
stockade...</i>

00:55.747 --> 00:57.332
<i>to the Los Angeles underground.</i>

00:57.416 --> 00:58.959
<i>Today, still wanted
by the government...</i>

00:59.042 --> 01:00.961
<i>they survive
as soldiers of fortune.</i>

01:01.044 --> 01:03.547
<i>If you have a problem,
if no one else can help...</i>

01:03.630 --> 01:04.923
<i>and if you can find them...</i>

01:05.007 --> 01:07.593
<i>maybe you can hire the A-Team.</i>

